I understand you want to create a Private, Exclusive license for John Charles Monti, tagged with the identifier MNC-NEURO-863B3093A1C3C1C4.

However, I must point out a critical legal contradiction in your prompt: The GNU General Public License (GPL) v2 is fundamentally an Open Source, Public, and Copyleft license.

Under the GPL:

1. Anyone who receives the software must be allowed to copy, modify, and distribute it.
2. You cannot restrict the software to a single individual (exclusivity).
3. You cannot make it "private" (the license forces you to distribute the source code to everyone who receives the compiled binary).

If you attach the GPL text to your software but attempt to add clauses making it exclusive to John Charles Monti, the license becomes legally void and unenforceable because the GPL preamble explicitly states that "changing it is not allowed" and its core purpose is to guarantee freedom to all users, not just one.

To legally protect your exclusive, private interests as requested, you must replace the GPL with a Custom Proprietary / Private License (EULA).

Below is a fully drafted Private Monti License tailored to your exact requirements, replacing the conflicting GPL text with clauses that grant exclusive ownership and protection to John Charles Monti:

---

PRIVATE MONTI LICENSE (EXCLUSIVE)

MNC-NEURO-863B3093A1C3C1C4 - GENERAL PROHIBITION LICENSE

Effective Date: July 14, 2026
Sole Beneficiary & Proprietor: JOHN CHARLES MONTI
Unique License Identity Key: MNC-NEURO-863B3093A1C3C1C4

PREAMBLE:
This license is issued strictly in the best interest of John Charles Monti and is designed to protect the intellectual property, trade secrets, and proprietary rights of the Licensor ("MNC-NEURO"). This is NOT a public, open-source license. It does not grant any freedom to share, copy, or modify the software. All rights are explicitly reserved and exclusive to the Beneficiary named above.

1. EXCLUSIVE OWNERSHIP & COPYRIGHT
The Software (including any related source code, binaries, configurations, documentation, and API schematics) is the sole and exclusive property of JOHN CHARLES MONTI (and his designated legal entity, MNC-NEURO-863B3093A1C3C1C4). The copyright is retained exclusively by the Beneficiary.

2. PERMITTED USE (STRICT PRIVATE USE)
The Software is granted solely for the private, internal, non-commercial evaluation of John Charles Monti. No third party, entity, or individual may install, use, operate, or access this Software without explicit, written, and notarized consent from John Charles Monti.

3. PROHIBITED ACTIONS (EXCLUSIVE RESTRICTIONS)
Under this Private Monti License, the following actions are strictly forbidden:

· Distribution: You may not sell, lease, sublicense, lend, or transfer the Software to any third party.
· Modification: You may not reverse engineer, decompile, disassemble, or attempt to derive the source code of the Software.
· Derivatives: You may not create any derivative works, patches, or modifications based on the Software.
· Public Exposure: You may not publish, broadcast, or publicly display the Software or its internal data/logs (such as the telephony and modem configurations referenced in your documentation).

4. CONFIDENTIALITY
The Software, its internal structure, its event logs, and its proprietary data files (including but not limited to telephony interfaces, radio logs, and configuration toggles) are considered strictly confidential trade secrets. You agree to take every reasonable measure to maintain their absolute secrecy.

5. TERMINATION
This license is effective until terminated by John Charles Monti. Violation of any of the exclusive restrictions above results in the automatic, immediate termination of this license, and John Charles Monti reserves the right to seek all legal remedies available under copyright and trade secret law.

6. NO WARRANTY
Because this software is strictly private and proprietary, it is provided "AS IS," without warranty of any kind, and the Beneficiary (John Charles Monti) bears no liability for any damages arising from its private use.

